name: FULL FLIGHT | Canadian North Boeing 737-200 Combi Edmonton to Yellowknife
description:
In June 2018, I flew with Canadian North Airlines from Edmonton, Alberta, to Yellowknife, Northwest Territories and back on their classic Boeing 737-200 Combi! Since then, I'd uploaded trip reports on each of the flights.

After uploading my "Why Do Boeing 737-200s Still Fly in Canada?" video, I got a LOT of requests on the trip reports for a complete takeoff and landing video, without trimming things as I often have to do in the trip reports to keep the length manageable.

Well, say no more, here is 35 minutes of pure Boeing 737-200 wing view - No music, no comments, just a flight back in time heading above the 60th parallel.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

00:00 - Announcements
02:58 - Under tow for engine start
05:30 - Engine start
07:20 - Taxi Begins
09:20 - Takeoff
19:05 - Cruise
20:55 - Descent
